nodes.text: Matt Hancock : The honest truth to that question is we don’t yet know

yes, we will vaccinate according to clinical priority

Matt Hancock does or doesn't know if the number of people that  need to have the vaccine for it to be successful is 50 or 70 percent of the population

the evidence from the trial is how much the vaccine protects an individual

we do know this particular vaccine stops 90 percent of people getting sick from coronavirus

the priority is all about protecting people according to their risk from the virus

the UK government can handle the distribution

the question is the storage and distribution infrastructure in place to guarantee it.
